                "invention-title": [
                    "Magnesium hydride-based hydrogen storage material and preparation method thereof",
                    "一种氢化镁基储氢材料及其制备方法"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention provides a magnesium hydride-based hydrogen storage material and a preparation method thereof, and belongs to the technical field of solid hydrogen storage new energy. High-hardness metal (manganese, titanium or zirconium) and raw materials of magnesium hydride are subjected to ball-milling, milling and mixing in a protective atmosphere, and the magnesium hydride-based hydrogen storage material is obtained after two times of cyclic activation. Magnesium hydride particles in the hydrogen storage system are dispersed and distributed in a high-hardness metal matrix, the magnesium hydride particles can be cooperatively milled and refined in the ball milling process, a rapid diffusion channel is provided for H-transfer, magnesium hydride grains are protected and inhibited from growing in the hydrogen absorption and desorption process, and the magnesium hydride grains are prevented from being agglomerated; and the hydrogen desorption temperature of magnesium hydride is obviously reduced."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明提出了一种氢化镁基储氢材料及其制备方法，属于固态储氢新能源技术领域。本发明通过将高硬度金属(锰、钛或锆)与氢化镁的原料在保护气氛下进行球磨铣削混合，经两次循环活化后得到氢化镁基储氢材料。该储氢体系中氢化镁颗粒弥散分布在高硬度金属基质中，可以在球磨过程中协同铣削、细化氢化镁颗粒，为H‑的转移提供了快速扩散通道，在吸放氢过程中保护并抑制氢化镁晶粒长大，防止氢化镁晶粒团聚；且显著降低了氢化镁的放氢温度。"
                }
            ]
        }
